review_title: BEST HP OMEN LAPTOP RTX 4050 WITH GREAT FEATURES AND PERFORMANCE AS WELL
review_text: i have used this laptop in depth since two weeks including gaming , movies, editing etc and depending upon that i have made the pros and cons as under which will guide and make it easy for new buyers that really matters while buying a gaming laptop .PROS -1) SOLID BUILD QUALITY FEELS SO PREMIUM METAL MADE.2) CPU AND GPU IS VERY FAST AND XTREMELY GOOD AT GAMING AND EDITING BOTH.3) DISPlAY QUALITY IS ALSO VERY GOOD AS WELL4) GEN 4 SSD EXTREMLY FAST FOR GAMING AND CREATIVE WORKS .5) BATTERY BACKUP IS DECENT LAST 3-4hrs max.6) SPEAKERS ARE REALLY LOUD AND GREAT SOUND QUALITY.7) RTX 4050 6Gb GPU REALLY GAVE 75-85 fps in high to ultra settings in most of the LATEST  AAA TITLE GAMES8) DDR5 5600MHZ RAM SUPER FAST9) FULL HD WEBCAM . GOOD QUALITY AS WELL.CONS-1) NO BAG INCLUDED2) ONLY ONE NVME SLOT FOR STORAGE , NO EXTRA SLOT AVAILABLE.  LAPTOPS NOWADAYS GOT MIN 2 NVME SLOTS FOR STORAGE UPGRADE , THAT IS REALLY WEIRD.3) INSTEAD OF 512gb , 1tb NVME SHOULD HAVE BEEN PROVIDED.REST ALL I CAN SAY A BEAUTIFUL GAMING LAPTOP UNDER 1 lakh ruppees. HOPE IT HELPS.

review_text: I bought it for 57k I guess... Overall laptop is good but after 5 months I noticed dead pixel on display...Then I contacted Asus service centre and they got it replaced... Then again after 2 months CPU side fan started making Buzzing noise... The service centre first denied to replace the fan as they said if the fan was not physically damaged they can't replace it... But eventually they had to replace it cause cleaning the fan had not solved my problem... Now it is ok but inside 1 year I faced this 2 problems that I personally think shouldn't happen for a new laptop. If you're buying this for gaming yes you can play AAA titles smoothly on medium or low settings... If u wanna play games in high or ultra settings the laptop will struggle. Another con is battery backup. Don't expect more than 3 to 3.5 hours battery backup on this laptop. And there are air vents below the laptop but all the vents are not open so the airflow I won't say is sufficient to keep the laptop cool during heavy working on this laptop.Overall I would say the laptop is good but if u can go 10 to 20k more bucks then go for a RTX GPU one ...

review_title: Let's Get Real: My Experience with DELL G15 Intel i5-12500H16GB
review_text:
The media could not be loaded.
                
            
                
            
        
    
    








  
  
    ¬†Hey there, fellow tech enthusiasts! I'm here to share my genuine experience with the DELL G15 Intel i5-12500H 16GB laptop. Buckle up, as I'm going to be totally candid about the ups and downs I encountered during my laptop-buying adventure.The Pros - What I Loved:-First things first, let's talk about the positives! The DELL G15 impressed me with its smooth handling and those fantastic mouse pad gestures. No more annoying lags or glitches when navigating around! Plus, the sturdy build quality gave me a sense of confidence that this laptop could withstand the test of time.One thing that pleasantly surprised me was that Windows, McAfee, and Office were pre-activated right out of the box. It saved me the hassle of dealing with those activations separately. The keyboard, overall, was a delight to type on. Although there was a slight issue during gaming, it didn't majorly impact my everyday usage.The Cons - The Not-So-Great Stuff:-Now, let's dive into the not-so-great aspects. If you're a hardcore gamer, this might not be the best pick for you. The keyboard gets quite toasty, and I found myself constantly adjusting the fan speed to manage the heat. Without an AC in the summer, it can be a real bummer.While the performance was generally good, I did face some hiccups during gaming, especially in PUBG. I couldn't figure out if it was because of the heat or high RAM consumption. Speaking of RAM, there's an issue with system usage that takes up almost 45% of the 16GB RAM even when there are no resource-intensive tasks running.I tried to tweak things by altering some settings in "msconfig" to reduce RAM usage, but it caused problems with the G alien shortcut key and audio jack. A bit of a trade-off there. The laptop is better suited for single-tasking, as running multiple Chrome tabs pushed the RAM utilization to 76-78%.As for battery life, it's not the most impressive, providing only about an hour of backup. The laptop is better suited for single-tasking, as running multiple Chrome tabs pushed the RAM utilization to 76-78%.As for battery life, it's not the most impressive, providing only about an hour of backup. So, if you're a person who needs long-lasting battery power, you might want to consider other options.Why I Made This Purchase:-Now, you might be wondering, "Why on earth did you buy it then?" Well, I had my reasons. My previous laptop experience with DELL's service support was excellent, so I trusted the brand blindly. Besides, I specifically wanted an Intel processor, and the DELL G15 checked that box perfectly.For my needs, smooth performance and everyday tasks were more important than gaming performance. I mostly use the laptop at home, so I didn't care much about its weight or gaming capabilities. Each person has their unique usage requirements, so consider your own needs before making a decision.The Bottom Line:-To cut to the chase, this laptop suits my personal requirements, but it does come with a fair share of cons. Be sure to weigh the pros and cons carefully before making your own choice. DELL's customer support, especially through WhatsApp, was a significant plus, and it helped me resolve some of the issues.Now regarding Pricing:-I got this DELL G15 for ‚Çπ67,527 on 15th July 2023. The original price was ‚Çπ72,990, but I received an instant discount of ‚Çπ908 through Amazon ICICI, and an additional ‚Çπ1,000 promotional discount was applied. With these discounts, the price reduced to ‚Çπ71,082. And here's the best part: I also received a cashback of ‚Çπ3,554 (5% ICICI Amazon credit card) in my Amazon wallet, further reducing the total cost. So, after considering all the discounts and cashback, the laptop cost me a fantastic ‚Çπ67,527 only.If you find a similar deal between ‚Çπ67,000 to ‚Çπ68,000, it's worth considering. Keep other options open if you're reading this in 2024.So, there you have it, my genuine review of the DELL G15. Keep in mind my experiences, and I hope this helps you in making an informed decision about your dream laptop! Happy tech-hunting!

review_text: Its an amazing laptop for 67k, & Very VFM for 60k (Credit Card discount offer). So wait for card offer and buy, if not in hurry.The i5 12500h - 12 core CPU is AMAZING.I'm mainly using it for design work (Solidworks) & the combination of 12500h & RTX 3050 makes my work easy.Gaming- using it with LG Ultragear 144hz Monitor -GTA5, CSGO, Forza H4, are all easy 144fps.Other games need little bit of tweaking to get 144 fps.Battery - to get most out out of battery, reduce laptop display refresh rate to 60Hz from 120.Google  "Windows 11 Processor power management" and Change the setting for "Maximum processor state" -> "on battery" to 50%.I'm getting 2.5 hours with basic MS Word, Chrome. You can try turning off nVidia GPU in BIOS to get more out of the battery.If you mostly use the laptop with AC power, then open "My Dell" app. - click on "Power" in app, set "Battery Charging Mode" to "Always AC".

But bluetooth mic should be of good quality.16) Runs hot during gaming.17) Medium weight laptop and a bit thick.18) Aluminium frame. Does leak a bit of current on the top of laptop when you touch it. It can be solved with proper earthing wire.19) Suggested to buy another keyboard and mouse so that you dont damage its keyboard inbuilt.20) Supports windows 11 home. Windows 11 pro can be bought on microsoft store if you want encryption of drives.(Bitlocker)21) 1080p resolution lcd screen.I think there are better laptops out there in this price range. Boots under 5 seconds.

review_title: Dont buy for Gaming !!! 8 Months usage Review
review_text:
The media could not be loaded.
                
            
                
            
        
    
    








  
  
    ¬†This lapotp is being advertised as a gaming laptop these days. I'd say it's not so, this is a Powerful Thin and Light laptop. Professionals go for it, Gamers AVOID IT!Okay why's that so, lemme explain the Cons of this for gaming: (I've upgraded my laptop to 16GB Gskill + 1.5TBs of SSD)TLDR: CPU THROTTLES AROUND 12-15W which drops the GPU Usage to 30-40% for any game due to CPU Bottleneck! Acer BIOS Power limits the CPU to 12W.1. The laptop Power adaptor is 90W, with dGPU rtx 2050 going upto 35W alone. This is a MaxQ version of the RTX 2050 which comes in newer budget gaming laptops.2. The GPU is not the issue for gaming here! Yes despite being 35W counterpart it's quite powerful as it's same Ampere based GPU 3050. RTX 3050 + 64Bit = RTX 2050.The real issue lie within the CPU power throttling!3. i5-1240P despite being much powerful CPU, goes upto 45W on inital full load giving awesome performance due to Intel SpeedStep technology, but short after few 10s seconds the CPU throttles around 12-15W TDP ONLY! THIS CAUSES THE CPU TO STUCK ONLY UPTO 0.9-1.1Ghz on full load! This makes any game shutter like hell after just few minutes of the gameplay!4. Thermals ain't a issue for performance! The Laptop has 2 fans which goes upto 6250RPM alone. I thought maybe due to temperature the CPU starts throttling but no even at 60¬∞C temprature (tested with 5Fan cooling pads) the CPU is stuck for the same load. Investing it further in XTU, It's the Acer BIOS Power limit which can't be changed unless acer decides to do something for an Bios update.Coming to the positive part, as i brought it for mostly work purposes apart my office laptop (I'm a Developer) these features are hard to find in any laptop in the segment:1. 12Th gen CPU 12/16 + 4GB RTX 2050. This ensures Coding workload on multiple IDEs, Running Android Emulator is easy!2. Latest Technologies which make it super portable: Thunderbolt 4 coming with Power delivery, Now i charge this and my office laptop with same Type C 60W PD charger of my phone. So You can just take a normal 60W PD charger!3. Wifi 6E is a cheery on top!4. One extra Nvme slot is a plus point!Overall:4.5/5 : Thin and Light portable laptop.1.5/5: Gaming Laptop.

review_title: Dont buy for Gaming !!! 8 Months usage Review
review_text:
The media could not be loaded.
                
            
                
            
        
    
    








  
  
    ¬†This lapotp is being advertised as a gaming laptop these days. I'd say it's not so, this is a Powerful Thin and Light laptop. Professionals go for it, Gamers AVOID IT!Okay why's that so, lemme explain the Cons of this for gaming: (I've upgraded my laptop to 16GB Gskill + 1.5TBs of SSD)TLDR: CPU THROTTLES AROUND 12-15W which drops the GPU Usage to 30-40% for any game due to CPU Bottleneck! Acer BIOS Power limits the CPU to 12W.1. The laptop Power adaptor is 90W, with dGPU rtx 2050 going upto 35W alone. This is a MaxQ version of the RTX 2050 which comes in newer budget gaming laptops.2. The GPU is not the issue for gaming here! Yes despite being 35W counterpart it's quite powerful as it's same Ampere based GPU 3050. RTX 3050 + 64Bit = RTX 2050.The real issue lie within the CPU power throttling!3. i5-1240P despite being much powerful CPU, goes upto 45W on inital full load giving awesome performance due to Intel SpeedStep technology, but short after few 10s seconds the CPU throttles around 12-15W TDP ONLY! THIS CAUSES THE CPU TO STUCK ONLY UPTO 0.9-1.1Ghz on full load! This makes any game shutter like hell after just few minutes of the gameplay!4. Thermals ain't a issue for performance! The Laptop has 2 fans which goes upto 6250RPM alone. I thought maybe due to temperature the CPU starts throttling but no even at 60¬∞C temprature (tested with 5Fan cooling pads) the CPU is stuck for the same load. Investing it further in XTU, It's the Acer BIOS Power limit which can't be changed unless acer decides to do something for an Bios update.Coming to the positive part, as i brought it for mostly work purposes apart my office laptop (I'm a Developer) these features are hard to find in any laptop in the segment:1. 12Th gen CPU 12/16 + 4GB RTX 2050. This ensures Coding workload on multiple IDEs, Running Android Emulator is easy!2. Latest Technologies which make it super portable: Thunderbolt 4 coming with Power delivery, Now i charge this and my office laptop with same Type C 60W PD charger of my phone. So You can just take a normal 60W PD charger!3. Wifi 6E is a cheery on top!4. One extra Nvme slot is a plus point!Overall:4.5/5 : Thin and Light portable laptop.1.5/5: Gaming Laptop.

review_text: I‚Äôve the same laptop with i7 9th gen.The graphic card is 1650 max q and same ssd.Only difference is this one comes with i7 11gen and 144hz refresh rate.Intro into my model.Gameplay was lil choppy at high settings and multiple browsers and tabs made it sweat. I added a 16gb ram to it now totalling to 24GB and I‚Äôve added a 165hz 2k led gaming monitor. One issue I found with this laptop is there‚Äôs no display port or thunderbolt output. Type c is only for data transfer and charging peripherals. So max refresh rate I‚Äôm getting through my Hdmi cable is 120hz and it still made a massive difference in valorant and other FPS games.Mine is 2 years old with a 9th gen i7 and still doesn‚Äôt break a sweat. I play gta 5 and valorant and farcry 6 in full graphics.Just add an 8 or 16gb ram and you‚Äôre good to go

review_text: Amazing product, if you are looking for an upgrade for your existing gaming laptop nothing beats this config in price to performance.I bought the 3070ti version with AMD 6000 series CPU at a price of 1.25 lacs. After months of research I couldn‚Äôt justify going for a Intel CPU (which are generally expensive comparatively) or the 4060 GPU which has a lower class bus width (performance wise both will be almost same due to increased architecture efficiency). I suggest looking into DLSS Frame generation tech more in case you really want a 40 Class GPU.I have overall been satisfied with this product in about a month‚Äôs time that I have used it. Also, I would suggest removing all bloatware manually (or you can do a clean windows install like I did) but make sure to get the latest OMEN SDK from HPs website to ensure you can control important parameters for performance.

name: HP Omen 16,AMD Ryzen 7 6800H,16.1 inch(40.9cm)QHD Gaming Laptop(16GB RAM/1TB SSD/NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3070ti 8GB Graphics/165Hz/3ms Response Time/Win 11/MSO 21/4Zone Backlit KB/B&O/Alexa/XBOX)16-n0123AX

review_text: You get what you pay for, which is mainly the graphics card in this package. Lot of corners have been cut to provide this graphics card at this price, but after 4 months of usage and heavy gaming, I don't think anyone is going to complain if they bought it purely for gaming bang for buck. Yes speakers suck, yes screen wobbles, yes it doesn't look like it's worth 1.27 lakh, but the target customer will be content.Edit: For those worried about Amazon's support, rest assured there is no need for Amazon's support. Just go to your nearest official HP Care service centre and only there. This model has official warranty from HP in India. My screen had freezing issues and I got it replaced by HP at my home itself within a week.

name: HP Omen 16,AMD Ryzen 7 6800H,16.1 inch(40.9cm)QHD Gaming Laptop(16GB RAM/1TB SSD/NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3070ti 8GB Graphics/165Hz/3ms Response Time/Win 11/MSO 21/4Zone Backlit KB/B&O/Alexa/XBOX)16-n0123AX
variant_data: {"B0CCVZP835":["GeForce RTX 4060"],"B0C2D1P9F8":["GeForce RTX 3070ti"]}
review_text: I had my eyes on a 3070ti laptop that cost more than 1.4L, and suddenly this laptop came up for sale. I was a bit intrigued about the ingenuity of the deal, however, as you can see, this laptop has it all and for a price of 98K after exchange, this is a steal!I'd like to share my experience with this device so far! The things I loved about this device are:- Amazing 165Hz panel, 1440p resolution, and crystal clear output. For me, it is the perfect resolution, as 1080p is just a bit low and 4k adds unnecessary pressure on the GPU, resulting in a waste of frames and power.- Powerful RTX 3070ti, that too with a max TGP of 150w. This is the solo feature that hooked me to this device. I mean with the TGP like this, you come so close to the max performance of its desktop variants.- Ryzen 7 6800h performs like a champ, both in speed and battery, due to its newer 6nm architecture.- I like OMEN gaming hub, the UI is clear, UX is friendly and I like that you can browse cool wallpapers directly through the app, yes I like to switch wallpapers, five times a day.Now, some of the things that not necessarily are bad for me, but could be for someone else:- Screen Shake is present, but not so aggressive as some YouTube reviews say it has.- The build could have been better, plastic is fine for me as this laptop is probably never going to leave my home desk, but a nice metal build would have been appreciated. But then the weight would have been more than 3.4 Kg, so it's fine what it is.If this comes for a sale! I'd suggest buying this device ASAP. or waiting for almost 6-8 months for the price drop of the newer 4000 series laptops, but, look for the TGP of those devices.

review_text: I bought this in Amazon Summer Sale @ 93.4k after applying ICICI credit card and Laptop exchange discount.Easily THE best deal I've ever come across in any product in any platform anywhere. This is simply the steal deal. Glad I bought this in time because now I can see its not available anymore.The laptop came on time and delivery was hassle free.Coming to Laptop -1. The build quality is solid and feels premium.2. Laptop hinge is sturdy and holds well (well slight wobble is noticable around frame but is manageable).3. Display is crisp and clear and colors are accurate.4. RTX 3070ti is the highlight of this laptop and you can check score in the pics.5. HP care pack is pre installed and warranty for 1 yr is already registered in their database.6. Keyboard is also beautiful and feels good to type.7. Thermals in this laptop are also decent.8. Extremely quick boot up time.9. AMD Ryzen 7 6800h also perfoms well.Cons -It is a sin to write any cons at this steal price point :)  !!!Unimaginable unbelievable DEAL feauturing nVidia RTX 3070ti seeing the present market condition makes this the STAR Gaming Laptop you could ever buy otherwise this would cost around 2.0 lacs minimum anywhere.TOTALLY WORTH IT!!!THANKS AMAZON FOR BRINGING THIS TO US üôåüôåüôå
